The calendar in the date picker numbers weeks (along the left). However it gets the week numbers wrong. It seems to be trying to implement the numbering scheme described in ISO-8601 (see [this summary|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Week#Week_number]):

{code}
/** Returns the number of the week in year, as defined in ISO 8601. */
Date.prototype.getWeekNumber = function() {
    var d = new Date(this.getFullYear(), this.getMonth(), this.getDate(), 0, 0, 0);
    var DoW = d.getDay();
    d.setDate(d.getDate() - (DoW + 6) % 7 + 3); // Nearest Thu
    var ms = d.valueOf(); // GMT
    d.setMonth(0);
    d.setDate(4); // Thu in Week 1
    return Math.round((ms - d.valueOf()) / (7 * 864e5)) + 1;
};
{code}

However it seems to be buggy (see for example week numbers in 2004). 

*update:*
There is a workaround for this issue in 3.13.x and 4.0.x. Thanks to Bettina Zucker for this solution. See the comment [here|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-9048?focusedCommentId=183463&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_183463].

Within the Issue Navigator _View & Hide_ screen - the *Text Query Summary* currently defines a search over multiple fields with an _AND_ - e.g.:

{panel}
Query:  "perforce NOT installation" in Summary *and* Description Fields
{panel}

The search is actually executed over each field and the results are combined - so this summary should use an _OR_ - e.g.:

{panel}
Query:  "perforce NOT installation" in Summary *or* Description Fields
{panel}

